munistic idea. It is sufficient, however, to note that </div><div class="t ma45 x14 h2d y1843 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">believers were being added every day,. and such a plan </div><div class="t m9f1 x14 h2d y18f3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">would have involved an inventory and a redistribution </div><div class="t m9e5 x14 h2d y1946 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">every day, which would have been an impossibility. </div><div class="t m460 x14 h2d y35a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">They simply parted with their possessions &quot; as every man </div><div class="t mf53 x14 h2d yb5f ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">had need.&quot; It was the natural outgrowth of the Spirit of </div><div class="t m354 x14 h2d y881 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ in the church, making all feel that they were mem- </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
